turn.2: Another Girl, Another Planet  "Another Girl, Another Planet" is the most successful song by the English rock band The Only Ones, whose members are Peter Perrett, Alan Mair, John Perry and Mike Kellie.
turn.4: It is the second track on their first album, "The Only Ones", released in 1978.
turn.6: The song has since been covered by several other performers.
turn.8: It was recorded on a 16-track analogue Studer tape machine and an ex-Steve Marriott Helios mixing console at Escape Studios, a residential facility in Egerton, Kent, England, by engineer/producer John Burns, assisted by Ian (now, Jennifer) Maidman, and later worked on and mixed at Basing Street Studios by Robert Ash.
turn.10: The track was not a chart hit upon its initial release in 1978.
turn.12: Its first chart appearance was 7th June 1981at No. 44, for one week, on the New Zealand chart.
